import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y='latitude', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['speed'] = pd.to_numeric(data['speed'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='red', label='Median Speed: {:.2f}'.format(data['speed'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['dirCat'] = pd.Categorical(data['dir'])
    data['dirCat'] = data['dirCat'].cat.codes
    sns.scatterplot(x='dirCat', y='speed', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between direction and speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['dirCat'] = data['dirCat'].astype('category')
    sns.countplot(x='dirCat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of direction categories?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['dirCat'] = data['dirCat'].astype(str)
    g = sns.FacetGrid(data, col='dirCat', col_wrap=3, height=4)
    g.map(sns.scatterplot, 'dir', 'speed', alpha=0.5)
    plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)
    g.fig.suptitle('What is the distribution of direction and speed for each direction category?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
